snippet: The UnitedHealth Group, the nation’s largest health insurer, said that revenue rose more than 11 percent in the fourth quarter, while net income slipped 1 percent.
lead_paragraph: The UnitedHealth Group, the nation’s largest health insurer, said that revenue rose more than 11 percent in the fourth quarter, while net income slipped 1 percent.

headline.seo: An Insurer, UnitedHealth, Reports a Slight Drop in Income
headline.main: Income at UnitedHealth Drops a Bit as Medical Costs Rise
